 {"id":"frankenpandas-review-inf01","title":"fix(columnar): python_mod_f64 returns nan for finite % infinity","description":"REVIEWER finding: The formula `lhs - floor(lhs/rhs) * rhs` in python_mod_f64 (line 611-612) produces nan for finite values modulo infinity where Python returns correct values:
- 5.0 % inf → should be 5.0, returns nan
- -5.0 % inf → should be inf, returns nan
- 5.0 % -inf → should be -inf, returns nan
- -5.0 % -inf → should be -5.0, returns nan

Root cause: floor(x/inf) * inf = 0 * inf = nan. Introduced in fe06882.

Fix: Add infinity check - if rhs.is_infinite(), return lhs when same sign, rhs when opposite sign.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cc_1","created_at":"2026-04-28T21:15:00.000000000Z","created_by":"cc_1","updated_at":"2026-04-28T22:35:00.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T22:35:00.000000000Z","close_reason":"Fixed in cb3f2d5 - added infinity check to python_mod_f64 with 10 test cases covering all combinations.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["reviewer","fp-columnar","modulo","infinity","edge-case"],"priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":null,"created_at":"2026-04-28T21:15:00.000000000Z","created_by":"cc_1","updated_at":"2026-04-28T21:15:00.000000000Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["reviewer","fp-columnar","modulo","infinity","edge-case"]}
